column168: XPO Logistics terminal XDM experienced a UN3349 Force 6.5G Insecticide release from (4) 40-pound cardboard boxes containing inner paper bags. ERTS dispatched contractors to conduct cleanup operations. Contractors arrived onsite and confirmed approximately 4 cups of product released to a 1’ x 1’ area of the metal and wooden trailer floor due to a forklift puncture. The damaged bags were collected along with all impacted PPE into a 55-gallon poly drum. The waste was staged onsite for terminal personnel to manage.

column168: XPO notified ERTS regarding a punctured metal drum containing hazardous product, Onyxide 200. The drum was punctured by a pallet nail and released approximately 1-quart of product onto the wooden trailer floor. A Contractor cleaned-up the release using rags. The damaged drum was overpacked and the rags/ppe were containerized for waste disposal. No storm-drains, waterways, or soil were impacted by the spill.
